### Configure UTC Timezone for Payload Admin Panel in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/admin/overview.mdx

Shows how to configure UTC as a timezone option in Payload CMS so that displayed dates match exactly what's stored in the database. When UTC is selected, editor input times like '1pm' will display as '1pm' and be stored as '13:00:00Z' in UTC format. This ensures no timezone conversion between display and storage.

```typescript
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

const config = buildConfig({
  // ...
  admin: {
    timezones: {
      supportedTimezones: [
        {
          label: 'UTC',
          value: 'UTC',
        },
        // ...other timezones
      ],
      defaultTimezone: 'UTC',
    },
  },
})
```

