### Configure Payload CMS `autoRun` Queue Processing

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/jobs-queue/queues.mdx

This snippet shows how job queuing and `autoRun` configuration interact with specific queues in Payload CMS. If a job is explicitly queued to a particular queue (e.g., 'critical') using `payload.jobs.queue()`, the `autoRun` configuration must explicitly specify that queue to be processed; otherwise, the job will not be picked up by the automatic runner.

```ts
// Queuing to 'critical' queue
await payload.jobs.queue({ task: 'myTask', queue: 'critical' })

// But autoRun only processes 'default' queue
autoRun: [{ queue: 'default' }] // won't pick up the job
```

