### Configure Priority-Based AutoRun Queues in Payload CMS buildConfig

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/jobs-queue/queues.mdx

This snippet shows how to define multiple 'autoRun' configurations within the Payload CMS 'buildConfig' for priority-based job processing. It sets up different cron schedules and 'limit' values for distinct queues ('critical', 'default', 'batch') to manage various levels of job urgency.

```ts
export default buildConfig({
  jobs: {
    tasks: [
      /* ... */
    ],
    autoRun: [
      {
        cron: '* * * * *', // Every minute
        limit: 100,
        queue: 'critical',
      },
      {
        cron: '*/5 * * * *', // Every 5 minutes
        limit: 50,
        queue: 'default',
      },
      {
        cron: '0 2 * * *', // Daily at 2 AM
        limit: 1000,
        queue: 'batch',
      },
    ],
  },
})
```

