### Define ScheduleConfig Type for Tasks and Workflows in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/jobs-queue/schedules.mdx

TypeScript type definition for configuring job schedules in Payload CMS. Requires cron expression and queue name, with optional beforeSchedule and afterSchedule hooks for customization. Supports seconds precision in cron expressions for fine-grained scheduling control.

```typescript
export type ScheduleConfig = {
  cron: string // required, supports seconds precision
  queue: string // required, the queue to push Jobs onto
  hooks?: {
    // Optional hooks to customize scheduling behavior
    beforeSchedule?: BeforeScheduleFn
    afterSchedule?: AfterScheduleFn
  }
}
```

