### Configure Custom Timezones for Payload Admin Panel in TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/admin/overview.mdx

Sets up a custom list of supported timezones for the Payload CMS Admin Panel using the admin.timezones configuration. This example defines three European timezones and sets Europe/Amsterdam as the default. Timezone values must be valid IANA timezone names validated against Intl.supportedValuesOf('timeZone').

```typescript
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

const config = buildConfig({
  // ...
  admin: {
    timezones: {
      supportedTimezones: [
        {
          label: 'Europe/Dublin',
          value: 'Europe/Dublin',
        },
        {
          label: 'Europe/Amsterdam',
          value: 'Europe/Amsterdam',
        },
        {
          label: 'Europe/Bucharest',
          value: 'Europe/Bucharest',
        },
      ],
      defaultTimezone: 'Europe/Amsterdam',
    },
  },
})
```

